title: const variables should not be hashed

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: E-needs-test
labels.description: Call for participation: writing correctness tests

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
It appears that the [template](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/new?labels=C-bug%2C+I-ICE%2C+T-compiler&template=ice.md) is no longer working.

I got this after running `cargo check` on a build that had no issues. I then ran `rustup update` and `cargo clean` to do a fresh build and still got the error. I know it isn't related to incremental builds and it's currently giving me a headache.
